repnme.cdata!:
Dahomey - Highway Maintenance and
            Engineering Project

abstracts.cdata!:
The project consists of: (a) a four-year
            highway maintenance program (PART I) providing for: (i) the
            strengthening and reorganization of the road maintenance
            organization; and (ii) the overhaul and renewal of the
            highway maintenance equipment fleet, reorganization of the
            maintenance shops and purchase of equipment for the soil
            laboratory; (b) detailed engineering and bidding documents
            for reconstruction of about 320 km of primary highway (PART II).

abstracts.cdata!:
The Highway Maintenance and Engineering
            Project for Dahomey consists of: (a) a four-year highway
            maintenance program (part one) providing for: (i) the
            strengthening and reorganization of the road maintenance
            organization; and (ii) the overhaul and renewal of the
            highway maintenance equipment fleet, reorganization of the
            maintenance shops and purchase of equipment for the soil
            laboratory; and (b) detailed engineering and bidding
            documents for reconstruction of about 320 km of primary
            highway (part two).
